Classification.Comment: The copy number gain of 11q12.2q13.5 involves numerous protein-coding genes. Grillo et al. (2014) report a patient with a de novo duplication of 11q13.3 with developmental delays and other variable phenotypes. Ziebart et al. (2013) describe a family with an inherited duplication of 11q13.3. There is an additional report of a family with spinocerebellar ataxia type 20 (OMIM 608687), in which all affected members have a duplication of 11q12.2q12.3 (Knight 2008). Thus, based on current medical literature and gene content, this copy number variant (CNV) is classified as pathogenic. References: Grillo et al., Gene. 2014 Jan 25;534(2):435-9. PMID: 24120895 Knight et al., Hum Mol Genet. 2008 Dec 15;17(24):3847-53. PMID: 18801880 Ziebart et al., Clin Oral Investig. 2013 Jan;17(1):123-30. PMID: 22297612
